Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.38,0:00:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我们有一件小事想让你知道\N{\rEN}There's a small matter we wanted to make you aware of.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.59,0:00:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,曾在游轮公司担任会计的詹姆斯·韦塞尔\N{\rEN}Former cruise employee, James Wiesel in accounting,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.84,0:00:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,好像被官司吓到了 而且...\N{\rEN}seems to have gotten spooked. And...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.30,0:00:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,看上去他有可能要开口了\N{\rEN}seems like he might be about to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.09,0:00:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我还以为我们把这一切都解决了呢\N{\rEN}I thought we had this all sewn up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.55,0:00:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,-我说的是希望如此  -不要...打断我\N{\rEN}-I said I'd hoped. -Don't... Interrupt me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.71,0:00:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你跟你爸谈过注入大笔投资\N{\rEN}Have you talked to your dad about a major injection
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.38,0:00:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至是将我们私有化吗\N{\rEN}or even taking us private?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.67,0:00:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,这事我们之间就可以谈\N{\rEN}It's a conversation we can have.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.92,0:00:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,敬比尔 有史以来最好的老板\N{\rEN}To Bill, the best boss that ever lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.84,0:00:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我要做个文档给你\N{\rEN}So I'm gonna create a word document for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.67,0:00:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我打印给你 因为我不想任何纸质材料上\N{\rEN}and then I'm gonna print it because I don't want anything
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.96,0:00:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,留有我的笔迹\N{\rEN}with my handwriting on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.34,0:00:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为瑞亚很危险 而且我认为我们必须阻止她\N{\rEN}I think Rhea is dangerous, and I think we need to stop her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.05,0:00:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要抛开个人恩怨 来一次家庭休战\N{\rEN}We need to put feelings aside and call a family truce.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.42,0:00:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,那 我们向韦塞尔先生提出了第二次\N{\rEN}So we made the second threat-slash-offer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.34,0:00:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,恩威并施的提议 他拒绝了\N{\rEN}to Mr. Wiesel, and he said, "No."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.96,0:00:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,新人会被撕成碎片\N{\rEN}The new face is gonna get ripped to shreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.71,0:00:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我真的在想瑞亚的问题 我看她看准了吗\N{\rEN}I really am wondering about Rhea. Have I got her right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.71,0:00:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,她最合适\N{\rEN}She's the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.21,0:00:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我将任命瑞亚·贾瑞尔\N{\rEN}I shall be appointing Rhea Jarrell
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.38,0:00:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,作为我的集团总裁\N{\rEN}as my Chief Executive Officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.13,0:01:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,这个狗屎帝国 是时候偿还一切了\N{\rEN}This empire of shit, time to pay up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.96,0:01:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上好 我是苏珊·瓦尔迪\N{\rEN}Good evening. I'm Susan Vardy,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.71,0:01:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,今晚重点报道 独家专访\N{\rEN}and in focus tonight, an exclusive interview
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.67,0:01:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,韦斯达·罗伊科集团举报者詹姆斯·韦塞尔\N{\rEN}with Waystar Royco whistleblower James Weissel.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.46,0:01:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,性剥削 暴力 盗窃\N{\rEN}Sexual exploitation, violence, theft,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.34,0:01:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,此外 还有许多其他罪行 全部隐藏在\N{\rEN}plus, a host of other crimes, all of it hidden
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.80,0:01:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,掩盖与腐败之下\N{\rEN}by cover-ups and corruption
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.42,0:01:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,-以避免负面新闻  -滴答滴答\N{\rEN}-to avoid damaging headlines... -Cha-ching.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.26,0:01:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,-黑幕 黑幕  -我们的嘉宾指控\N{\rEN}- Book deal, book deal! -That's what my guest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.01,0:01:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,上述现象在"明亮星" 美国第二大\N{\rEN}alleges went on for decades inside Brightstar,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.30,0:02:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,游轮运营公司 内部存在了数十年\N{\rEN}America's second-largest cruise line operator.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.51,0:02:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,那 詹姆斯 您在明亮星见证了一些可怕的事情\N{\rEN}So, James, you witnessed some terrible things at Brightstar.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.21,0:02:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,最让您感到困扰的是什么\N{\rEN}What disturbed you the most?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.92,0:02:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯 苏珊...\N{\rEN}Well, Susan...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.30,0:02:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"好吧 苏珊 我是个垃圾\N{\rEN}"Well, Susan, I'm a piece of shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.01,0:02:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-我是黄鼠狼 我很害怕 "  -明亮星游轮是一个\N{\rEN}-I'm a weasel, and I'm scared." -Brightstar Cruises was,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.88,0:02:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,几十年来 管理不善的大粪坑……\N{\rEN}for decades, a cesspool of mismanagement...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.96,0:02:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,数十年来支付了数百万美元\N{\rEN}and millions and millions of dollars paid out over decades
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.21,0:02:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,以掩盖由明亮星的员工提供的\N{\rEN}to cover up sexual exploitation and harassment
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.30,0:02:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,性剥削和性骚扰 其中很多事情\N{\rEN}by Brightstar employees, and a lot of it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.84,0:02:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,实际上是由当时的负责人莱斯特·麦克林托克犯下的\N{\rEN}actually committed by the man in charge, Lester McClintock.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.30,0:02:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,-莫叔叔  -莫·麦克林托克\N{\rEN}-Uncle Mo. -Mo McClintock.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.51,0:02:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,谁能忘了我们的老莫\N{\rEN}Who could forget our Mo?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.34,0:02:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,而且 还有更严重的事件\N{\rEN}Then you have even more serious incidents
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.05,0:02:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,发生在美国管辖范围之外\N{\rEN}occurring outside of U.S. Jurisdiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.38,0:02:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,来宾落水 受伤 以及原因不明的死亡\N{\rEN}Guests overboard, injury, and, uh, unexplained deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.96,0:02:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,那您怎么看待这些事件\N{\rEN}And what are you saying about these incidents,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.42,0:02:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,包括乘客落水这样的情况\N{\rEN}including passengers overboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.63,0:02:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,-我什么都不知道  -噢\N{\rEN}-I don't know everything. -Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.17,0:02:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,他现在什么都不知道了\N{\rEN}He doesn't know everything now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.01,0:02:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,但是 我知道故事的内容\N{\rEN}But I know what the stories were,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.80,0:02:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,而且我很清楚 没有任何...\N{\rEN}and I do know that there was no appetite...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.01,0:02:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,证据在哪里 露丝\N{\rEN}Yeah, where's the proof, Ruth?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.63,0:02:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,...高层管理人员有意向\N{\rEN}...whatsoever from the senior management
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.17,0:03:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,去揭露真相\N{\rEN}for uncovering the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.01,0:03:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,是谁在支持你 黄鼠狼 嗯\N{\rEN}Yeah, who's backing you, weasel? Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.01,0:03:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,-你是说有人在掩盖这些事吗  -绝对的\N{\rEN}-You're saying there were cover-ups? -Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.92,0:03:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,还有那些人 下船的人 公司总部的人\N{\rEN}And people, people off the ship, the company HQ,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.80,0:03:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,他们知道正在进行这种掩盖吗\N{\rEN}did they know this sort of cover-up was going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.51,0:03:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 公司确实有一些人在负责监管 嗯...\N{\rEN}Well, there was there a certain amount of oversight, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.21,0:03:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,格丽·科尔曼...\N{\rEN}Gerri Kellman...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.34,0:03:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,-格丽  -韦斯达的总顾问格丽·科尔曼\N{\rEN}-Gerri! -Gerri Kellman, the Waystar general counsel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.63,0:03:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,-格丽警报  -...她说 要优先考虑\N{\rEN}-Gerri alert! -...saying no bad PR
